caption.p: Fig. 2: Genotyping of CHIKV strains (n=10) identified in Rio de Janeiro during the outbreak occurred in 2016. Neighbor Joining method (A) and Maximum-Likelihood (B), both K2 parameters model, bootstrap of 1,000 replications. The CHIKV sequences analyzed are represented by black circles. CHIKV strains were named as follows: GenBank accession number (or name strain)/country/year. The O'nyong nyong virus was used as outgroup.
